.Dd April 17, 2026
.Dt HYRULE 4
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm hyrule
.Nd Hyrulian Kernel Interface and World Map
.Sh SYNOPSIS
To compile this driver into the kernel,
place the following line in your
kernel configuration file:
.Bd -ragged -offset indent
.Cd "device hyrule"
.Ed
.Pp
Alternatively, to load the driver as a
module at boot time, place the following line in
.Xr loader.conf 5 :
.Bd -ragged -offset indent
.Cd "hyrule_load=\*qYES\*q"
.Ed
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
module provides a virtual representation of the Land of Hyrule within the
.Xr devfs 5
filesystem.
It creates a hierarchical structure under
.Pa /dev/hyrule/
allowing users to interact with characters, objects, and their properties through
standard file operations.
.Pp
Characters and objects are organized as follows:
.Pa /dev/hyrule/{type}/{name}/{category}/{property}
.Pp
The module also features a world map system. Link's position is tracked on a 10x10
grid. Users can move Link and configure the map through dedicated device nodes.
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width ".Pa /dev/hyrule/map" -compact
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/console/power
Power switch for the console. Write '1' to turn on (and reset), '0' to turn off.
If the cartridge is dusty, power-on may fail randomly.
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/console/reset
Reset button. Write '1' to restore all character stats and map to default values.
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/console/cartridge
Represents the game cartridge. Can be 'clean' or 'dusty'.
If 'dusty', reading other devices may result in random graphics glitches.
Write 'blow' to this device to clean the cartridge and stabilize the system.
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/console/cpu
Provides detailed system statistics in JSON format, including CPU execution ticks
and per-core temperatures (via
.Xr coretemp 4
or
.Xr amdtemp 4 ) .
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/game/save
Save device. Reading from this device provides a serialized state of the game
that can be redirected to a file.
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/game/load
Load device. Writing a previously saved state to this device restores the game session.
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/help
A help device providing usage instructions.
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/map
Displays the current state of the Hyrulian world map, including Link's position
denoted by 'L'.
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/world/map_config
A configuration device for the 10x10 map grid. Lowercase characters represent
accessible terrain, while uppercase characters represent blocked areas.
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/console/controller/
A directory containing controller nodes (up, down, left, right, a, b).
The directional devices (up, down, left, right) only appear if Link can move in that direction.
Reading or writing to these devices will move Link. The 'a' and 'b' buttons are
general-purpose action buttons that can be mapped to items.
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/map/local/
A dynamic directory containing nodes for local exploration. If Link is standing
on an entrance (e.g., a Cave 'C', Shop 'S', or Dungeon '1-3'), a corresponding node (e.g.,
.Pa cave ,
.Pa shop ,
or
.Pa dungeon1 )
will appear. Reading this node will move Link inside.
.Pp
Once inside a dungeon, several nodes appear:
.Bl -tag -width ".Pa map/local/treasure" -compact
.It Pa map/local/room
Describes the current room.
.It Pa map/local/next
Moves Link to the next room in the dungeon.
.It Pa map/local/prev
Moves Link to the previous room.
.It Pa map/local/treasure
Found in room 4 of each dungeon. Reading this node grants a new weapon.
.It Pa map/local/boss
Found in room 9 of each dungeon. Defeating the boss grants a Triforce piece.
.It Pa map/local/exit
Allows returning to the world map (only available in the entrance room).
.El
.Pp
Collecting Triforce pieces enables sword upgrades at the Upgrade Cave ('U'):
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
0 Triforces: Wooden Sword
.It
1 Triforce: White Sword
.It
2 Triforces: Master Sword
.It
3 Triforces: Access to Ganon's Castle ('G')
.El
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/characters/link/items/
A directory containing Link's inventory. Items found in the world, such as the
.Pa sword ,
will appear here.
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/characters/
Directory containing character data (health, stamina, rupees).
.It Pa /dev/hyrule/objects/
Directory containing object data (Triforce).
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
To see the system statistics:
.Pp
.Dl "cat /dev/hyrule/console/cpu"
.Pp
To see the current world map:
.Pp
.Dl "cat /dev/hyrule/map/view"
.Pp
To explore a cave when Link is at a 'C' location:
.Pp
.Dl "cat /dev/hyrule/map/local/cave"
.Pp
To equip and use the Sword:
.Pp
.Dl "echo 'characters/link/items/sword' > /dev/hyrule/console/controller/a"
.Dl "cat /dev/hyrule/console/controller/a"
.Pp
To see the current status of Link's health:
.Pp
.Dl "cat /dev/hyrule/characters/link/stats/health"
.Pp
To equip Link with a new weapon:
.Pp
.Dl "echo 'Master Sword' > /dev/hyrule/characters/link/weapons/sword"
.Pp
To save the current game state:
.Pp
.Dl "cat /dev/hyrule/game/save > mysave.sav"
.Pp
To reload a previously saved game:
.Pp
.Dl "cat mysave.sav > /dev/hyrule/game/load"
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr kldload 8 ,
.Xr kldunload 8
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
module first appeared in April 2026 as a demonstration of a game-like kernel interface.
